name: Abort
tooltip: Stops the execution of a list of **ACTIONS** in a **RULE**.

name: AbortIf %1
tooltip: Stops the execution of a list of **ACTIONS** in a **RULE** if the provided **Bool** is **_True_**. Otherwise, the execution continues with the remaining **ACTIONS**.

name: AbsoluteValue %1
tooltip: Returns the unsigned value of the provided **Number** input.

name: Add %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the sum of two **Number** or two **Vector** values.

name: And %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** value based on whether both of the provided inputs return **_True_**.

name: AngleBetweenVectors %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the angle (in degrees) between two provided **Vector** values.

name: AngleDifference %1 %2 %3 %4
tooltip: Returns the difference between two angles (in degrees).

name: AppendToArray %1 %2
tooltip:
Returns a copy of an **Array** with the provided value appended to the end.  
  
_Note: It is not possible for an array to contain arrays. Attempting to append an array to an array will concatenate them instead._

name: ApplyMedGadget %1 %2
tooltip: Applies the effect of a medical gadget to a target **Player**.

name: ArccosineInDegrees %1
tooltip: Returns the inverse cosine of a provided **Number** value in degrees.

name: ArccosineInRadians %1
tooltip: Returns the inverse cosine of a provided **Number** value in radians.

name: ArcsineInDegrees %1
tooltip: Returns the inverse sine of a provided **Number** value in degrees.

name: ArcsineInRadians %1
tooltip: Returns the inverse sine of a provided **Number** value in radians.

name: ArctangentInDegrees %1
tooltip: Returns the inverse tangent of a provided **Number** value in degrees.

name: ArctangentInRadians %1
tooltip: Returns the inverse tangent of a provided **Number** value in radians.

name: ArrayContains %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** value based on whether the provided **Array** contains the provided value.

name: ArraySlice %1 %2 %3 %4 %5
tooltip: Returns a copy of the specified **Array** containing only values from a specified index range.

name: BackwardVector
tooltip: Returns the backward directional **Vector** of (0, 0, 1).

name: Bool
tooltip:
A **Bool** is fancy game developer talk for a **_True_** or **_False_** value. This type is used to define or identify the state of a variety of things.  
  
Is a player currently prone?  
  
Is the player using a specific soldier?  
  
Can players not score points because of some custom condition?

name: Break
tooltip: Breaks and exits the execution of a looping block, such as **While** or **LoopVariable**.

name: CapturePointCapturingTime %1 %2
tooltip: Sets the capturing time for target **CapturePoint** to the provided **Number**.

name: CapturePointNeutralizationTime %1 %2
tooltip: Sets the neutralization time for target **CapturePoint** to the provided **Number**.

name: CapturePoints
tooltip: Returns a **CapturePointsItem** from the collection of all possible capture points.

name: Ceiling %1
tooltip: Returns the value rounded up to the nearest integer.

name: ClearAllCustomMessages %1 %2 %3
tooltip: Clears all custom messages for a provided **Player** or **TeamId**. If no **Player** or **TeamId** is provided, it will clear all custom messages for everyone.

name: ClearCustomMessage %1 %2 %3 %4
tooltip: Clears text from the provided **CustomMessageSlotsItem** for the provided **Player** or **TeamId**. If no **Player** or **TeamId** is given, it clears all players text at that **CustomMessageSlotsItem**.

name: ClosestPlayerTo %1 %2 %3 %4
tooltip:
Returns the closest alive **Player** to a provided position. Can be filtered using a **TeamId**.  
  
_Note: If no players are alive when this block is called, the returned **Player** will be invalid._

name: CompareCapturePoint %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if the target **CapturePoint** has the same designation as the provided **CapturePointsItem**.

name: CompareVehicleName %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if the target **Vehicle** has the same name as the provided **VehiclesItem** or if it is the same type as the provided **VehicleTypesItem**.

name: CONDITION %1
tooltip: Evaluates the condition to run a **RULE** or **SUBROUTINE** block based on the **Bool** input.

name: Continue
tooltip: Forces the execution of a looping block (such as **While** or **LoopVariable**) to the start of the next iteration of that block.

name: CosineFromDegrees %1
tooltip: Returns the cosine value of a specified angle in degrees.

name: CosineFromRadians %1
tooltip: Returns the cosine value of a specified angle in radians.

name: CountOf %1
tooltip: Returns the **Number** of elements in the specified **Array**.

name: CreateVector %1 %2 %3 %4 %5 %6
tooltip: Returns a **Vector** composed of three provided 'X' (left), 'Y' (up), and 'Z' (forward) values.

name: CrossProduct %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the cross product between two **Vector** values. If the two **Vector** inputs are parallel, the result will be zero.

name: CurrentArrayElement
tooltip: Returns a reference to the current **Array** element being evaluated. Only used for **FilteredArray**, **MappedArray**, **SortedArray**, **IsTrueForAll**, and **IsTrueForAny**.

name: CustomMessageSlot
tooltip: Returns a **CustomMessageSlotsItem** which can be used with **DisplayCustomMessage** and **ClearCustomMessage** to display information on screen to players.

name: DamageTypes
tooltip: Returns a **DamageTypesItem** from the collection of all possible damage types.

name: DamageVehicle %1 %2
tooltip: Damages the target **Vehicle** by the provided **Number** amount.

name: DealDamage %1 %2 %3 %4 %5 %6
tooltip: Deals a provided amount of damage to a target **Player** by a another **Player**.

name: DeathTypes
tooltip: Returns a **DeathTypesItem** from the collection of all possible death types.

name: DegreesToRadians %1
tooltip: Returns a value in radians from a specified value in degrees.

name: DeployAllPlayers
tooltip: Force spawns all players in the deploy screen.

name: DeployPlayer %1
tooltip: Deploys a target **Player** onto the battlefield from the deploy screen.

name: DestroyVehicle %1
tooltip: Destroys the target **Vehicle**.

name: DirectionFromAngles %1 %2 %3 %4
tooltip: Returns a directional **Vector** from the provided horizontal (yaw) and vertical (pitch) angles (in degrees).

name: DirectionTowards %1 %2 %3 %4
tooltip: Returns the direction, or normalized **Vector**, from a starting position and ending position.

name: DisplayCustomMessage %1 %2 %3 %4 %5 %6 %7
tooltip:
Display a **Message** on-screen in the upper right corner. Using the **CustomMessageSlotsItem**, this **Message** can be displayed on multiple lines. It will stay up for the length of the provided duration, or stay up indefinitely if a negative **Number** is provided. It will be displayed to everyone unless a specific **Player** or **TeamId** is provided.  
  
_Note: It's your responsibility to ensure a safe and fair experience for others, violating the EA User Agreement by using offensive or inappropriate text may result in account bans._

name: DisplayGameModeMessage %1 %2 %3
tooltip:
Displays a **Message** on the top center of the screen for 6 seconds. If no target is provided, the **Message** will display to everyone.  
  
_Note: This will only appear to players that are deployed on the map. It's your responsibility to ensure a safe and fair experience for others, violating the EA User Agreement by using offensive or inappropriate text may result in account bans._

name: DisplayHighlightedWorldLogMessage %1 %2 %3
tooltip:
Displays a **Message** on the world log above the minimap for 6 seconds. If no target is provided, it will display the **Message** to everyone.  
  
_Note: This will only appear to players that are deployed on the map. It's your responsibility to ensure a safe and fair experience for others, violating the EA User Agreement by using offensive or inappropriate text may result in account bans._

name: DisplayNotificationMessage %1 %2 %3
tooltip:
Displays a notification-type **Message** on the top-right of the screen for 6 seconds. If no target is provided, it will display the **Message** to everyone.  
  
_Note: It's your responsibility to ensure a safe and fair experience for others, violating the EA User Agreement by using offensive or inappropriate text may result in account bans._

name: DistanceBetween %1 %2 %3 %4
tooltip: Returns the distance between a starting position and ending position.

name: Divide %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the ratio between two **Number** values or a **Vector** and **Number** value. A **Vector** divided by a **Number** will yield a scaled **Vector**.

name: DotProduct %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the dot product between two **Vector** values. If the two values are orthogonal to each other, the result will be zero.

name: DownVector
tooltip: Returns the downward directional **Vector** of (0, -1, 0).

name: Else
tooltip: The start of a block of **ACTIONS** that will execute if all previous **If** and **ElseIf** conditions are **_False_**.

name: ElseIf %1
tooltip: The start of a block of **ACTIONS** that will run if its condition is **_True_** and all previous **If** or **ElseIf** conditions are **_False_**.

name: EmptyArray
tooltip: Returns an initialized empty **Array**.

name: EnableAllInputRestrictions %1 %2
tooltip: Enables or disables all keyboard and mouse inputs - such as movement, firing, and turning - for a target **Player**.

name: EnableAllPlayerDeploy %1
tooltip: Enables or disables spawning from the deploy screen for all players.

name: EnableCapturePointDeploying %1 %2
tooltip: Enables or disables deploying on provided **CapturePoint** for the team that owns it.

name: EnableCapturing %1 %2
tooltip: Enables or disables capturing a provided **CapturePoint**.

name: EnableDefaultGameModeScoring %1
tooltip: Enables or disables default gamemode scoring logic, which refers to the base gamemode's scoring rules. For instance, disabling this rule will remove ticket bleed from Conquest or add one point for kills in Free-for-All. Disable this if you want to implement your own custom scoring logic.

name: EnableDefaultGameModeWinCondition %1
tooltip: Enables or disables the gamemode's default win condition logic. The win condition is checked when the time limit is reached or when a team or player reaches the target score. Disable this if you want to trigger your own win condition.

name: EnableGameModeObjective %1 %2
tooltip:
Enables or disables the provided **CapturePoint** or **MCOM**.  
  
_Note: MCOMs are only available on TDM, VTDM, and Custom Conquest layouts._

name: EnableHQ %1 %2 %3 %4
tooltip:
Enables or disables a headquarters specified by the provided **TeamId** and **Number** index.  
  
_Note: The index begins counting at 0_.

name: EnableInputRestriction %1 %2 %3
tooltip: Enables or disables a specified **InputRestrictionsItem** on a target **Player**.

name: EnablePlayerDeploy %1 %2
tooltip: Enables or disables the ability for a target **Player** to deploy.

name: EnableTicketBleedAcceleration %1
tooltip: Enables or disables ticket bleed acceleration for both teams. Ticket bleed acceleration is on by default and only comes into effect if one team owns all sectors for about 60 seconds.

name: EnableVOMessaging %1
tooltip:
Enables or disables the gamemode voice-over (VO) text and audio messaging, such as announcements about sector majority and capture points.  
  
_Note: This function is enabled by default._

name: EnableWorldIconImage %1 %2
tooltip: Enables or disables the image for a provided **WorldIconsItem**.

name: EnableWorldIconText %1 %2
tooltip:
Enables or disables the text for a provided **WorldIconsItem**.  
  
_Note: There is no default text, and will need to be set before or after this property is enabled to appear_.

name: EndGameMode %1
tooltip: Ends the current gamemode and designates the provided **Player** or **TeamId** as the winner. The gamemode ends in draw if TeamId is set to 0.

name: Equals %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if two values are equal to each other.

name: EventCapturePoint
tooltip: Returns the **CapturePoint** payload from the **RULE** **EVENT** context.

name: EventDamageType
tooltip: Returns the **DamageType** of the victim from the **OnPlayerDamaged** **EVENT** context.

name: EventDeathType
tooltip: Returns the **DeathType** of the victim from the **OnPlayerDied** or **OnPlayerEarnedKill** **EVENT** context.

name: EventMCOM
tooltip: Returns a **MCOM** payload from the **RULE** **EVENT** context.

name: EventOtherPlayer
tooltip: Returns the 2nd **Player** payload from the **RULE** **EVENT** context.

name: EventPlayer
tooltip: Returns the 1st **Player** payload from the **RULE** **EVENT** context.

name: EventSeat
tooltip: Returns the **Number** seat index payload of a **Vehicle** from the **RULE** **EVENT** context.

name: EventTeam
tooltip: Returns the **TeamId** payload from the **Ongoing** Team **EVENT** context.

name: EventVehicle
tooltip: Returns the **Vehicle** payload from the **RULE** **EVENT** context.

name: EventWeapon
tooltip: Returns the **HardwareId** of the weapon used to kill the victim from the **OnPlayerDied** or **OnPlayerEarnedKill** **EVENT** context.

name: Factions
tooltip: Returns a **FactionsItem** from the collection of all available factions.

name: FarthestPlayerFrom %1 %2 %3 %4
tooltip:
Returns the farthest alive **Player** from a provided position. Can be filtered using a **TeamId**.  
  
_Note: If no players are alive when this block is called, the returned **Player** will be invalid._

name: FilteredArray %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a filtered version of the specified **Array** based on the condition provided. This block cycles through the entire array. You can utilize the **CurrentArrayElement** block to represent the element in the **Array** for each iteration. For an **Array** like **GetPlayers**, **CurrentArrayElement** would represent each **Player** in that **Array**. You can then build your filter condition based on a property of that **Player** (like score, or some custom player **Variable** value).

name: FirstOf %1
tooltip: Returns the first value of the specified **Array**.

name: Floor %1
tooltip: Returns the value rounded down to the nearest integer.

name: ForceAllExitVehicle %1
tooltip: Forces all players to exit the target **Vehicle**.

name: ForceMandown %1
tooltip: Puts the target **Player** into the mandown state (unless mandown is disabled).

name: ForcePlayerExitVehicle %1 %2
tooltip: Forces the specified **Player** to exit the target **Vehicle**.

name: ForcePlayerToSeat %1 %2 %3
tooltip:
Forces the specified **Player** into the target **Vehicle** at the provided seat **Number**.  
  
_Note: If the provided index is -1, that **Player** will be forced into the first available seat._

name: ForceRevive %1
tooltip: Revives a target **Player** that is in the mandown state.

name: ForceSwitchInventory %1 %2
tooltip: Forces the target **Player** to switch to the provided **PlayerInventorySlotsItem**.

name: ForwardVector
tooltip: Returns the forward directional **Vector** of (0, 0, -1).

name: GetAllCapturePoints
tooltip: Returns an **Array** of all capture points within a game.

name: GetAllMCOMs
tooltip: Returns an **Array** of all MCOMs within a game.

name: GetAllPlayersInVehicle %1
tooltip: Returns a **Array** of all players inside a provided **Vehicle**

name: GetAllVehicles
tooltip: Returns an **Array** of all vehicles within a game.

name: GetCapturePointPosition %1
tooltip: Returns the in-world position of the provided **CapturePoint**.

name: GetCaptureProgress %1
tooltip: Returns a **Number** from zero to one corresponding to the capture progress of the provided **CapturePoint**.

name: GetCurrentOwnerTeamID %1
tooltip: Returns the current owner **TeamId** corresponding to the provided **CapturePoint**.

name: GetGameModeScore %1
tooltip: Returns the current gamemode score of the provided **Player** or **TeamId**.

name: GetGameModeTargetScore
tooltip: Returns the gamemode target score needed for victory.

name: GetGameModeTimeElapsed
tooltip: Returns the total elapsed time of the current gamemode.

name: GetGameModeTimeLimit
tooltip: Returns the time limit set for the gamemode (in seconds).

name: GetGameModeTimeRemaining
tooltip: Returns the amount of time left (seconds) in the current gamemode.

name: GetInventoryAmmo %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the target **Player** loaded ammo of the provided **PlayerInventorySlotsItem**.

name: GetInventoryMagazineAmmo %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the target **Player** magazine ammo of the provided **PlayerInventorySlotsItem**.

name: GetMCOMState %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the value of the target **MCOM** state.

name: GetObjective %1
tooltip: Returns the **CapturePoint** or **MCOM** corresponding to the provided **CapturePointsItem** or **MCOMsItem** respectively.

name: GetOwnerProgressTeamID %1
tooltip: Returns the **TeamId** of the team currently capturing the provided **CapturePoint**.

name: GetPlayerDeaths %1
tooltip: Returns the total amount of deaths for the target **Player**.

name: GetPlayerFromVehicleSeat %1 %2
tooltip:
Returns the **Player** currently occupying the provided seat index **Number** of the provided **Vehicle**.  
  
_Note: If no players are in the vehicle seat when this block is called, the returned **Player** will be invalid._

name: GetPlayerKills %1
tooltip: Returns the total amount of kills for the target **Player**.

name: GetPlayers
tooltip: Returns an **Array** of all players within a game.

name: GetPlayersOnPoint %1
tooltip: Returns a **Array** of all players within the boundaries of a provided **CapturePoint**.

name: GetPlayerState %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the value of the target **Player** state.

name: GetPlayerVehicleSeat %1
tooltip: Returns the seat index **Number** for the target **Player** if they are in a vehicle, otherwise returns -1.

name: GetPreviousOwnerTeamID %1
tooltip: Returns the previous owner **TeamId** corresponding to the provided **CapturePoint**.

name: GetRemainingFuseTime %1
tooltip: Returns the remaining fuse time (in seconds) on the provided **MCOM**.

name: GetSeatCount %1
tooltip: Returns the **Number** of seats in a **Vehicle**.

name: GetSubroutineArgument
tooltip: Returns the value of the argument that is passed into the **SUBROUTINE**. The list of available parameters will populate once this block is placed inside the **SUBROUTINE**.

name: GetTeamId %1
tooltip: Returns the **TeamId** value of the specified **Player** OR the corresponding **TeamId** of the provided **Number**.

name: GetVariable %1
tooltip: Returns the value of a **Variable**.

name: GetVehicleFromPlayer %1
tooltip: Returns the **Vehicle** used by a **Player**.

name: GetVehicleState %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the value of the target **Vehicle** state.

name: GetVehicleTeamId %1
tooltip:
Returns the **TeamId** of the provided **Vehicle**.  
  
_Note: A **Vehicle** that is not occupied will have a neutral **TeamId**._

name: GetXComponent %1
tooltip: Returns the 'X' component of a provided **Vector**.

name: GetYComponent %1
tooltip: Returns the 'Y' component of a provided **Vector**.

name: GetZComponent %1
tooltip: Returns the 'Z' component of a provided **Vector**.

name: GreaterThan %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if the 1st provided value is greater than the 2nd provided value.

name: GreaterThanEqualTo %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if the 1st provided value is greater than the 2nd provided value.

name: HasInventory %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if the provided **Player** has the specified ability.

name: Heal %1 %2 %3 %4 %5 %6
tooltip:
Instantly adds a given amount of health to the target **Player** applied by a healer **Player**.  
  
_Note: When healing a player with a max health multiplier not equal to 1, the amount of health they receive will scale with their max health multiplier value._

name: If %1
tooltip: The start of a conditional control block whose **ACTIONS** will execute if its condition is **_True_**.

name: IfThenElse %1 %2 %3 %4 %5
tooltip: Returns the 1st provided value if the condition is **_True_**, otherwise, returns the 2nd provided value.

name: IndexOfArrayValue %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the index of an **Array** value.

name: InputRestrictions
tooltip: Returns a **InputRestrictionsItem** from the collection of all inputs which can be restricted with **EnableInputRestriction**.

name: InventoryCharacterSpecialties
tooltip: Returns an **InventoryCharacterSpecialtiesItem** from the collection of all character specialties.

name: InventoryClassGadgets
tooltip: Returns an **InventoryClassGadgetsItem** from the collection of all class gadgets.

name: InventoryMeleeWeapons
tooltip: Returns an **InventoryMeleeWeaponsItem** from the collection of all melee weapons.

name: InventoryOpenGadgets
tooltip: Returns an **InventoryOpenGadgetsItem** from the collection of all open gadgets.

name: InventoryPrimaryWeapons
tooltip: Returns an **InventoryPrimaryWeaponsItem** from the collection of all primary weapons.

name: InventorySecondaryWeapons
tooltip: Returns an **InventorySecondaryWeaponsItem** from the collection of all secondary weapons.

name: InventoryThrowables
tooltip: Returns a **InventoryThrowablesItem** from the collection of all throwables.

name: IsCurrentMap %1
tooltip: Returns **_True_** if the provided **MapsItem** is the name of the current map.

name: IsFaction %1 %2
tooltip: Returns **_True_** if the provided **TeamId** is using soldiers from the specified **FactionsItem**.

name: IsInventorySlotActive %1 %2
tooltip: Returns **_True_** whether or not the active inventory slot of the target **Player** is the provided **PlayerInventorySlotsItem**.

name: IsKillerWeapon %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if the given **HardwareId** is equivalent to the provided ability.

name: IsPlayerUsingSoldier %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if the target **Player** is a specified **PlayerSoldiersItem**.

name: IsPlayerValid %1
tooltip: Returns **_True_** if the provided **Player** is valid.

name: IsTrueForAll %1 %2
tooltip: Returns **_True_** if the provided condition is **_True_** for every element in the provided **Array**.

name: IsTrueForAny %1 %2
tooltip: Returns **_True_** if the provided condition is **_True_** for at least one element in the provided **Array**.

name: IsType %1 %2
tooltip: Returns **_True_** if the provided value is equal to the specified **TypesItem**.

name: IsVehicleOccupied %1
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if the target **Vehicle** is a occupied by a player.

name: IsVehicleSeatOccupied %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if the target seat index **Number** of target **Vehicle** is a occupied by a player.

name: IsVictimDamageType %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if the victim was damaged by the provided **DamageType**.

name: IsVictimDeathType %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if the victim died by the provided **DeathType**.

name: Kill %1
tooltip: Kills a target **Player** (skips the Mandown state).

name: LastOf %1
tooltip: Returns the value at the end of the specified **Array**.

name: LeftVector
tooltip: Returns the leftward directional **Vector** of (-1, 0, 0).

name: LessThan %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if the 1st provided value is less than the 2nd provided value.

name: LessThanEqualTo %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if the 1st provided value is less than or equal to the 2nd provided value.

name: LocalToWorldPosition %1 %2 %3
tooltip: Converts the provided local **Player** position to the corresponding position in the world space.

name: LocalToWorldVector %1 %2 %3
tooltip: Converts the provided local **Player** vector to the corresponding vector in the world space.

name: LocationalSounds
tooltip: Returns a **LocationalSoundsItem** from the collection of locational sounds.

name: LoopVariable %1 %2 %3 %4 %5 %6 %7
tooltip: The start of a series of **ACTIONS** that will execute in a loop, modifying the control variable on each iteration. If the control **Variable** reaches or passes the range end value, the loop exits, and execution continues through the remaining **ACTIONS** in the **RULE**.

name: MappedArray %1 %2 %3
tooltip: Returns a copy of the provided **Array** with the values evaluated using the mapped expression provided. The following example utilizes the **GetPlayers** **Array** with **GetGameModeScore** and **CurrentArrayElement** to return an **Array** of **Player** scores.

name: Maps
tooltip: Returns a **MapsItem** from the collection of all maps.

name: Max %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the greater of the two **Number** values provided.

name: MCOMs
tooltip: Returns a **MCOMsItem** from the collection of all possible MCOMs.

name: MCOMStateBool
tooltip: Returns the **MCOMStateBoolItem** of the selected **Bool**-based MCOM property.

name: MedGadgetTypes
tooltip: Returns a **MedGadgetTypesItem** from the collection of medical gadget types which can be used with the **ApplyMedGadget**.

name: Message %1 %2 %3 %4 %5 %6 %7
tooltip:
Returns a constructed **Message** object which can be used with **DisplayGameModeMessage**, **DisplayNotificationMessage**, **DisplayHighlightedWorldLogMessage**, and **DisplayCustomMessage**. The **Message** object is created by providing a **Number**, **Player**, or format **String** (which can take up to 3 format items).  
A format **String** is a **String** that contains `{}` (called braces) within them, which can be substituted for parameters. For example, the **String** - `{} gained {} points!` - can be given a **Player** and **Number** parameter and could output as `John gained 2 points!`. See the example below for how this can be used with blocks.  
  
_Note: It's your responsibility to ensure a safe and fair experience for others, violating the EA User Agreement by using offensive or inappropriate text may result in account bans._

name: MOD
tooltip: Anything you want to work within your custom gamemode must be placed inside this block. You can put blocks you're working on outside of this block but they will not be executed. You can utilize the space outside the **MOD** block as a brainstorming area.

name: Modulo %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the remainder of the 1st provided value divided by the 2nd provided value.

name: Multiply %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the product of two **Number** values or the product of a **Vector** and **Number** value.

name: Normalize %1
tooltip: Returns a unit-length normalization of a **Vector**.

name: Not %1
tooltip: Return a **Bool** of the opposite value of the **Bool** input.

name: NotEqualTo %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** indicating if two values are not equal to each other.

name: Number
tooltip:
You can enter any numerical value you want here.  
1, 2, 3.14, -10.2  
  
Use this block in combination with math blocks to do all sorts of fun mathematical equations.

name: Or %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a **Bool** based on whether either of the two inputs are **_True_**.

name: PauseGameModeTime %1
tooltip: Pauses or unpauses the gamemode timer based on the provided **Bool** input.

name: Pi
tooltip: Returns the constant value 3.14159

name: PlayerInventorySlots
tooltip: Returns a **PlayerInventorySlotsItem** from the collection of all available player inventory slots.

name: PlayerSoldiers
tooltip: Returns a **PlayerSoldiersItem** from a list of all soldiers.

name: PlayerStateBool
tooltip: Returns the **PlayerStateBoolItem** of the selected **Bool**-based player property.

name: PlayerStateNumber
tooltip: Returns the **PlayerStateNumberItem** of the selected **Number**-based player property.

name: PlayerStateVector
tooltip: Returns the **PlayerStateVectorItem** of the selected **Vector**-based player property.

name: RadiansToDegrees %1
tooltip: Returns a value in degrees from a specified value in radians.

name: RaiseToPower %1 %2 %3 %4
tooltip: Returns the 1st provided value raised to the power of the 2nd provided value.

name: RandomizedArray %1
tooltip: Returns a copy of the specified **Array** with the values in a random order.

name: RandomReal %1 %2 %3 %4
tooltip: Returns a random **Number** between a specified minimum and maximum value (inclusive).

name: RandomValueInArray %1
tooltip: Returns a random value from the specified **Array**.

name: RemoveFromArray %1 %2
tooltip: Returns a copy of the specified **Array** with the provided value removed.

name: RemovePlayerInventory %1 %2
tooltip: Removes a specified inventory item from a target **Player** if that item is equipped.

name: RemovePlayerInventoryAtSlot %1 %2
tooltip: Removes the inventory from a target **Player** at the provided **PlayerInventorySlotsItem**.

name: RepairVehicle %1 %2
tooltip:
Repairs target **Vehicle** by the provided **Number** amount.  
  
_Note: When repairing a vehicle with a max health multiplier not equal to 1, the amount of health they receive will scale with their max health multiplier value._

name: ReplacePlayerInventory %1 %2
tooltip: Gives a target **Player** a new inventory item.

name: ResetGameModeTime
tooltip: Resets the gamemode time to its starting value.

name: Resupply %1 %2
tooltip: Resupplies the target **Player** using a provided **ResupplyTypesItem**.

name: ResupplyTypes
tooltip: Returns a **ResupplyTypesItem** from the collection of resupply types which can be used with **Resupply**.

name: RightVector
tooltip: Returns the rightward directional **Vector** of (1, 0, 0).

name: RoundToInteger %1
tooltip: Returns a whole **Number** rounded from the input value. The value rounds up if the decimal of the **Number** is greater than or equal to 0.5, and rounds down if it is less than 0.5.

name: RULE
tooltip:
**RULE** blocks are triggered from an in-game **EVENT**. When an **EVENT** triggers, this block will check if its **CONDITION** has been met and then execute all of the **ACTIONS**.  
**Types of **RULE** Blocks Events**
**Ongoing**
Ongoing **EVENT** types continually check if its **CONDITION** has become **_True_**. If so, the **ACTIONS** will be executed once. In order for the **EVENT** to execute again, the **CONDITION** must become **_False_** before becoming **_True_** again.  
   
Ongoing **EVENT** types currently exist within the context of:  
  
- **Global**  
- **Player**  
- **Team**  
- **Vehicle**  
- **CapturePoint**  
  
Within the **Player** and **Team** contexts, payload value blocks, such as **EventPlayer** and **EventTeam**, can be used to refer to the specific **Player** or **Team** within the **EVENT**. _Note: In FFA, Ongoing **Team** will not execute at all._
**OnPlayerDied**
This will trigger whenever a **Player** dies. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Victim), **EventOtherPlayer** (Killer), **EventDeathType** (Victim Death Type), **EventWeapon** (Killing Weapon)_
**OnPlayerDeployed**
This will trigger whenever a **Player** deploys. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Deployed Player)_
**OnPlayerJoinGame**
This will trigger when a **Player** joins the game. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Joined Player)_
**OnPlayerLeaveGame**
This will trigger when any player leaves the game.
**OnPlayerEarnedKill**
This will trigger when a **Player** earns a kill against another **Player**. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Killer), **EventOtherPlayer** (Victim), **EventDeathType** (Victim Death Type), **EventWeapon** (Killing Weapon)_
**OnGameModeEnding**
This will trigger when the gamemode ends.
**OnMandown**
This will trigger when a **Player** is forced into the mandown state. _Payloads: **EventPlayer**  (Downed Player)_
**OnRevived**
This will trigger when a **Player** is revived by another **Player**. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Revived Player), **EventOtherPlayer** (Reviver Player)_
**OnTimeLimitReached**
This will trigger when the gamemode time limit has been reached.
**OnGameModeStarted**
This will trigger at the start of the gamemode.
**OnPlayerUndeploy**
This will trigger when the **Player** dies and returns to the deploy screen. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Dead Player)_
**OnVehicleDeployed**
This will trigger when a **Vehicle** is called into the map. _Payloads: **EventVehicle** (Spawned Vehicle)_
**OnVehicleDestroyed**
This will trigger when a **Vehicle** is destroyed. _Payloads: **EventVehicle** (Destroyed Vehicle)_
**OnPlayerEnterVehicle**
This will trigger when a **Player** enters a **Vehicle**. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Player Who Enters), **EventVehicle** (Vehicle)_
**OnPlayerExitVehicle**
This will trigger when a **Player** exits a **Vehicle**. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Player Who Exits), **EventVehicle** (Vehicle)_
**OnPlayerEnterVehicleSeat**
This will trigger when a **Player** enters a **Vehicle** seat. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Player Who Enters Seat), **EventVehicle** (Vehicle), **EventSeat** (Seat Index)_
**OnPlayerExitVehicleSeat**
This will trigger when a **Player** exits a **Vehicle** seat. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Player Who Exits Seat), **EventVehicle** (Vehicle), **EventSeat** (Seat Index)_
**OnCapturePointCaptured**
This will trigger when a team takes control of a **CapturePoint**. _Payloads: **EventCapturePoint** (Captured Capture Point)_
**OnCapturePointCapturing**
This will trigger when a team begins capturing a **CapturePoint**. _Payloads: **EventCapturePoint** (Capture Point Being Captured)_
**OnCapturePointLost**
This will trigger when a team loses control of a **CapturePoint**. _Payloads: **EventCapturePoint** (Lost Capture Point)_
**OnCapturePointNeutralizing**
This will trigger when a team begins neutralizing a **CapturePoint**. _Payloads: **EventCapturePoint** (Capture Point Being Neutralized)_
**OnPlayerEnterCapturePoint**
This will trigger when a **Player** enters a **CapturePoint** capturing area. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Player Entering Capture Area), **EventCapturePoint** (Capture Point Being Entered)_
**OnPlayerExitCapturePoint**
This will trigger when a **Player** exits a **CapturePoint** capturing area. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Player Exiting Capture Area), **EventCapturePoint** (Capture Point Being Exited)_
**OnMCOMArmed**
This will trigger when a **MCOM** is armed. _Payloads: **EventMCOM** (Armed MCOM), **EventPlayer** (Player Who Armed)_
**OnMCOMDefused**
This will trigger when a **MCOM** is defused. _Payloads: **EventMCOM** (Defused MCOM), **EventPlayer** (Player Who Defused)_
**OnMCOMDestroyed**
This will trigger when a **MCOM** is destroyed. _Payloads: **EventMCOM** (Destroyed MCOM)_
**OnPlayerDamaged**
This will trigger when a **Player** takes damage. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Damaged Player), **EventOtherPlayer** (Damager Player), **EventDamageType** (Damage Type), **EventWeapon** (Damager Weapon)_
**OnPlayerEarnKillAssist**
This will trigger when a **Player** earns a kill assist. _Payloads: **EventPlayer** (Assist Player), **EventOtherPlayer** (Victim)

name: SendErrorReport %1
tooltip: Displays a provided **Message** as an error in the Admin menu.

name: SetCaptureMultiplier %1 %2
tooltip: Sets the capture time multiplier for target **CapturePoint** to the provided **Number**.

name: SetGameModeScore %1 %2
tooltip: Sets the gamemode score of the provided **Player** or **TeamId**.

name: SetGameModeTargetScore %1
tooltip: Sets the gamemode target score used to determine victory.

name: SetGameModeTimeLimit %1
tooltip: Sets the duration of the game in seconds.

name: SetInventoryAmmo %1 %2 %3
tooltip: Sets the target **Player** loaded ammo for the provided **PlayerInventorySlotsItem**.

name: SetInventoryMagazineAmmo %1 %2 %3
tooltip: Sets the target **Player** magazine ammo for the provided **PlayerInventorySlotsItem**.

name: SetMCOMFuseTime %1 %2
tooltip: Sets the fuse time (in seconds) for target **MCOM** to the provided **Number**

name: SetNeutralizationTimeMultiplier %1 %2
tooltip: Sets the neutralization time multiplier for target **CapturePoint** to the provided **Number**.

name: SetObjectiveOwner %1 %2
tooltip: Claims the provided **CapturePoint** for the specified **TeamId**.

name: SetPlayerMaxHealth %1 %2
tooltip:
Sets the max health of a target **Player** from 0 to 1000.  
  
_Note: The value will be multiplied by the max health multiplier of the that target._

name: SetPlayerSoldier %1 %2
tooltip: Sets a target **Player** soldier using a provided **PlayerSoldiersItem**. The soldier selected should be one that is available from that player team's faction, otherwise, the soldier will not be set. (_ex. if a team's faction is Bad Company 2 US, that player may only select Bad Company 2 US soldiers_).

name: SetRedeployTime %1 %2
tooltip:
Overrides the time to redeploy for a target **Player**.  
  
_Note: The redeploy time must be set to a value between 0 and 60 seconds._

name: SetTeamId %1 %2
tooltip:
Sets the target **Player** team using the provided **TeamId**. This will force the **Player** back to the deploy screen.  
  
_Note: this block is not supported in Free-For-All._

name: SetVariable %1 %2
tooltip: Sets the value of a **Variable**.

name: SetVariableAtIndex %1 %2 %3 %4 %5
tooltip:
Finds or initializes an **Array** on a provided **Variable**, and stores a provided value in that **Array** at the specified index.  
  
_Note: The first value in the array starts at an index of 0._

name: SetVehicleMaxHealthMultiplier %1 %2
tooltip:
Multiplies the maximum health of target **Vehicle** by the provided **Number** greater than 0 and less than or equal to 4.  
  
_Note: The health of a **Vehicle** is displayed in-game as a percentage._

name: SetWorldIconImage %1 %2
tooltip: Sets the image property of a **WorldIconsItem** to the selected **WorldIconImagesItem**.

name: SetWorldIconOwner %1 %2
tooltip: Sets the owner **TeamId** of the provided **WorldIconsItem**.

name: SetWorldIconPosition %1 %2
tooltip: Sets the in-world position of a provided **WorldIconsItem**.

name: SetWorldIconText %1 %2
tooltip: Sets the text property for a provided **WorldIconsItem**.

name: SineFromDegrees %1
tooltip: Returns the sine value of a specified angle in degrees.

name: SineFromRadians %1
tooltip: Returns the sine value of a specified angle in radians.

name: Skip %1
tooltip: Skips a provided number of **ACTIONS** following this block within this **RULE**.

name: SkipIf %1 %2
tooltip: Skips a provided number of **ACTIONS** following this block within this **RULE** if the condition evaluates to **_True_**. If it does not, execution continues with the remaining **ACTIONS**.

name: SkipMandown %1 %2
tooltip:
Sets the target **Player** to skip the mandown state and go directly to the deploy screen when killed.  
  
_Note: By default, **SkipMandown** is disabled._

name: SortedArray %1 %2 %3
tooltip: Returns a sorted version of the specified **Array** given a **Number** value to sort by (ascending). **CurrentArrayElement** can be utilized to represent each value in the **Array**. In the following example, **CurrentArrayElement** is used to represent each **Player** in **GetPlayers**. **GetGameModeScore** is used with **CurrentArrayElement** to return the score, used as a rank, to sort the **Array** in ascending order.

name: Sounds
tooltip: Returns a **SoundsItem** from the collection of sounds.

name: SpotTarget %1 %2 %3
tooltip: Spots a target **Player** for all players for a specified duration of time (in seconds).

name: SpotTargetForPlayer %1 %2 %3 %4 %5 %6
tooltip: Spots a target **Player** only for a specified **Player** for a provided duration of time (in seconds).

name: SquareRoot %1
tooltip: Returns the square root of a provided **Number** value.

name: StopTrackingVariable %1
tooltip: Stops an in-progress tracking of a **Variable** from the **TrackVariableOverTime** or **TrackVariableAtRate** blocks, leaving it at its current value.

name: String
tooltip:
You can use this block to utilize text within your mod.  
  
> Team 2s Flag has been Captured!  
>  
> A player has become the Juggernaut. Beware!  
>  
> Phase 3 of your really cool custom mod has started!  
  
_Note: It's your responsibility to ensure a safe and fair experience for others, violating the EA User Agreement by using offensive or inappropriate text may result in account bans._

name: SUBROUTINE
tooltip:
**SUBROUTINE** blocks are special blocks that are similar to **RULE** blocks, but do not have a designated **EVENT**. A **SUBROUTINE** block's **ACTIONS** will be executed when called from the **RULE** block. Like **RULE** blocks, **SUBROUTINE** blocks can have a **CONDITION** to determine whether or not the **ACTIONS** inside should execute.
  
  An important note is payload values, including **EventPlayer**, **EventOtherPlayer**, and **EventTeam**, use the context of the **RULE** block in which the **SUBROUTINE** instance block is placed in. An example of this would be, if your **RULE** block has an instance of **EventPlayer**, and the **SUBROUTINE** is called in **OnPlayerDeployed**, it would use the **EventPlayer** associated with **OnPlayerDeployed**. Be careful with this, as you will run into errors if your **SUBROUTINE** is placed inside a **RULE** block with non-existant payloads for that **EVENT**.

name: subroutineInstanceBlock
tooltip: Calls a **SUBROUTINE** block of the same name.

name: Subtract %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the difference between two **Number** values or two **Vector** values.

name: TangentFromDegrees %1
tooltip: Returns the tangent value of a specified angle in degrees.

name: TangentFromRadians %1
tooltip: Returns the tangent value of a specified angle in radians.

name: Teleport %1 %2 %3 %4 %5
tooltip: Teleports a target to a provided valid position facing a specified angle (in radians).

name: TrackVariableAtRate %1 %2 %3 %4 %5
tooltip:
Gradually modifies the value of a **Variable** at a specified rate (value/second) until it reaches the provided limit.   
  
_Note: If the limit is changed later, the **Variable** will continue to be updated from its previous value. To spot modifying the **Variable**, use **StopTrackingVariable**._

name: TrackVariableOverTime %1 %2 %3 %4 %5
tooltip:
Gradually modifies the value of a **Variable** over time (in seconds). The variable's value will reach the limit at the end of the interval.   
  
_Note: If the limit is changed later, the **Variable** will continue to be updated from its previous value. To spot modifying the **Variable**, use **StopTrackingVariable**._

name: TriggerAudio %1 %2
tooltip: Plays a provided **SoundsItem** or **VoiceOversItem** to a provided **TeamId**.

name: TriggerAudioAtLocation %1 %2
tooltip: Plays a selected **LocationalSoundsItem** at a specified position.

name: Types
tooltip: Returns a **TypesItem** from the collection of all object types.

name: UndeployAllPlayers
tooltip: Undeploys all players that are alive on the battlefield back to the deploy screen.

name: UndeployPlayer %1
tooltip: Undeploys a target **Player** that is alive on the battlefield back to the deploy screen.

name: UnspotTarget %1
tooltip: Unspots a target **Player** for all players.

name: UpVector
tooltip: Returns the upward directional **Vector** of (0, 1, 0).

name: ValueInArray %1 %2
tooltip: Returns the value found at a provided index of an **Array**.

name: Variable
tooltip:
This block is used to reference a **Variable** instance. The **Variable** can be selected by setting the scope -  **Global** , Player, or Team - in the first dropdown, and then selecting the **Variable** name in the second dropdown.  
  
**Variable** instances can be created or deleted by clicking on the _Variables_ tab, and clicking on _Manage Variables_.

name: VectorTowards %1 %2 %3 %4
tooltip: Returns the displacement **Vector** from a starting position to an ending position.

name: Vehicles
tooltip: Returns a **VehiclesItem** from the **Vehicle** collection.

name: VehicleStateVector
tooltip: Returns the **VehicleStateVectorItem** of the selected **Vector**-based vehicle property.

name: VehicleTypes
tooltip: Returns a **VehicleTypesItem** from the collection of all **Vehicle** types.

name: VoiceOvers
tooltip: Returns a **VoiceOversItem** from the collection of voice overs.

name: Wait %1
tooltip: Pauses the execution of **ACTIONS** in a **RULE** for a provided **Number** of seconds.

name: WaitUntil %1 %2
tooltip: Pauses the execution of **ACTIONS** in a **RULE** for a provided **Number** of seconds or if the provided condition evaluates to **_True_** during that interval.

name: While %1
tooltip:
A block of **ACTIONS** that will execute in a loop as long as the provided condition is **_True_**.  
  
_Note: You must utilize a **Wait** block at the beginning or the end of the iteration._

name: WorldIconImages
tooltip: Returns a **WorldIconImagesItem** from the collection of world icon images.

name: WorldIcons
tooltip: Returns a **WorldIconsItem** from the collection of world icon entities.

name: WorldToLocalPosition %1 %2 %3
tooltip: Converts the provided world position to the corresponding position in local **Player** space.

name: WorldToLocalVector %1 %2 %3
tooltip: Converts the provided world vector to the corresponding vector in local **Player** space.

name: Xor %1 %2
tooltip: Returns **_True_** if the provided **Bool** inputs return different values.

name: Break
tooltip: Break out of a loop

name: Continue
tooltip: Continue to the next iteration of a loop

name: If %1 Then %2
tooltip: Execute actions if condition is true

name: While %1 Do %2
